aders' Best Album (''Everything Must Go'') of 1996 \u2013 ''Hot Press''\n* Writers' Best Album (''Everything Must Go'') of 1996 \u2013 ''[[The Guardian]]''\n* Ivor Novello Award for Best Contemporary Song (A Design For Life), 1996\n* 7th Best Band of All Time \u2013 1999 ''NME'' Best Ever Category<ref name=NME1999>{{cite web|url=http://www.rocklistmusic.co.uk/1999.html |title=Rocklist.net...NME End Of Year Lists 1999 |website=Rocklistmusic.co.uk |date=9 May 1992 |accessdate=29 April 2017}}</ref>\n* 7th Best Album of All Time (''The Holy Bible'') \u2013 1999 ''NME'' Best Ever Category<ref name=\"NME1999\"/>\n* 8th Best Single of All Time (''A Design For Life'') \u2013 1999 ''NME'' Best Ever Category<ref name=\"NME1999\"/>\n* Best Internacional Rock Group \u2013 [[Eska Music Awards]], Poland, 2008\n* The MOJO Maverick Award 2009<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mojo4music.com/honours2009/2009/06/mojo_honours_list_09_the_winners.shtml |title=''Mojo'' Honours List '09, The Winners! (''Mojo'' Honours 2009) |website=[[Mojo (magazine)|mojo4music.com]] |date=26 March 2008 |accessdate=2 March 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506083117/http://www.mojo4music.com/honours2009/2009/06/mojo_honours_list_09_the_winners.shtml |archivedate=6 May 2012  }}</ref>\n* Songwriting Prize at the Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards, 2011\n* Ambassadors of Rock \u2013 [[Silver Clef Award]] 2012\n* Musician's Union Maestro (for [[James Dean Bradfield]]) at the Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards, 2013\n* The Ivors Inspiration Award at the Ivor Novello Awards, 2015\n{{Col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n* {{cite book |last=Price |first=Simon |title=Everything (A Book About Manic Street Preachers) |publisher=Virgin Books |place=London |isbn=0-7535-0139-2 |year=1999 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Clarke |first=Martin |title=Manic Street Preachers: Sweet Venom |year=1997 |publisher=Plexus |location=London |isbn=0-85965-259-9 |ref=harv}}\n\n