{"title_page": "Hakim Ziyech", "text_new": "{{short description|Dutch-Moroccan footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Hakim Ziyech\n| image = Por-Mar (14).jpg\n| caption = Ziyech with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname = Hakim Ziyech<ref>{{cite web |url=https://images.cafonline.com/image/upload/caf-prd/kpakgtavgq0lbzxizu89.pdf |title=Morocco |publisher=Confederation of African Football |page=16 |date=15 June 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|3|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Dronten]], Netherlands\n| height = 1.81 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ajax.nl/teams/ajax-1/selectie/speler/hakim-ziyech.htm?dbpage=426352|title=Hakim Ziyech|website=Ajax}}</ref>\n| position = [[Attacking midfielder]]<br>[[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]\n| clubnumber = 22\n| youthyears1 = 2001\u20132004\n| youthclubs1 = Reaal Dronten<ref>{{cite news|title=Behalve Asv Dronten hoopt ook Reaal op geld uit transfer Ziyech naar Ajax|url=https://dedrontenaar.nl/sport/behalve-asv-dronten-hoopt-ook-reaal-op-geld-uit-transfer-ziyech-naar-ajax|accessdate=14 October 2016|work=dedrontenaar.nl|date=1 September 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref>\n| youthyears2 = 2004\u20132007\n| youthclubs2 = ASV Dronten\n| youthyears3 = 2007\u20132012\n| youthclubs3 = [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs1 = [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]]\n| caps1 = 36\n| goals1 = 11\n| years2 = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs2 = [[FC Twente|Twente]]\n| caps2 = 68\n| goals2 = 30\n| years3 = 2016\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]\n| caps3 = 111\n| goals3 = 38\n<!-- DO NOT add Chelsea until he actually arrives at Chelsea and starts playing for them. He's still at Ajax for the rest of the season -->\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\n| nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U20]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 3\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2013\u20132014\n| nationalteam3 = [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 3\n| nationalgoals3 = 2\n| nationalyears4 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 32\n| nationalgoals4 = 14\n| club-update = 23:46, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 07:42, 29 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Hakim Ziyech''' ({{lang-ar|\u062d\u0643\u064a\u0645 \u0632\u064a\u0627\u0634}}; born 19 March 1993) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].\nIn 2019, he was selected as one of the 20 best players in the [[UEFA Champions League]] for the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the season|2018\u201319 season]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |title=UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2607890.html |work=UEFA.com |date=2 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theguardian.com/global/ng-interactive/2019/dec/17/the-100-best-male-footballers-in-the-world-2019| title = the best footballers in the world 2019 | publisher = the guardian.com | accessdate = 20 Dec 2019}}</ref> He is known for his finishing, [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]], long passes, technique, and ability from [[Direct free kick|free kicks]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/hakim-ziyech/ | title = Hakim Ziyech | publisher = worldfootball.net | accessdate = 26 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://eredivisielive.nl/eredivisie/speler/1079667/hakim-ziyech/ | title = Hakim Ziyech | publisher = eredivisielive.nl | accessdate = 26 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nZiyech started his professional career at Dutch club [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]] in 2012 and signed for fellow Dutch club [[FC Twente|Twente]] two years later.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> The [[2015\u201316 Eredivisie|2015\u201316]] season was the most prolific season in Ziyech's career, as he scored 17 goals and provided 10 assists in the Eredivisie.<ref name=\":2\" /> In 2016, Ziyech signed for Ajax on a five-year deal, with a reported transfer fee of \u20ac11m.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n\nIn February 2020, it was announced Ziyech would be joining [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for the [[2020\u201321 Premier League|2020\u201321 season]]. Chelsea would pay a transfer fee of \u20ac40 million plus possible bonuses to Ajax.\n\nZiyech was eligible to play for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] or [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref name=\"Football Oranje\" /> In 2015, he confirmed his choice to represent [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] at the international stage.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" /> He was selected for the final [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Morocco|23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name=\":7\" /><ref name=\":8\" />\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Heerenveen===\nZiyech was born in [[Dronten]], in the Netherlands. Between 2001 and 2007, he played for the youth academy of Reaal Dronten and ASV Dronten. In 2007, he joined the Heerenveen academy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dedrontenaar.nl/sport/behalve-asv-dronten-hoopt-ook-reaal-op-geld-uit-transfer-ziyech-naar-ajax|title=Behalve Asv Dronten hoopt ook Reaal op geld uit transfer Ziyech naar Ajax|date=1 September 2016|work=DeDrontenaar.nl|access-date=3 August 2018|language=nl-NL}}</ref>\n\n====2012\u201313 season====\nOn 2 August 2012, Ziyech made his formal debut for [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]] in the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Heerenveen v Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|first leg]] of the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Third qualifying round|third qualifying round]] of the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], against [[FC Rapid Bucure\u0219ti|Rapid Bucure\u0219ti]], playing a total of 53 minutes before being substituted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/matches/round=2000354/match=2009789/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League \u2013 Heerenveen-Rapid Bucure\u015fti|last=UEFA.com|website=UEFA.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> He made his [[Eredivisie]] debut for the club on 10 August, in a 0\u20132 loss to [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/191811/eredivisie-sc-heerenveen-nec/|title=SC Heerenveen \u2013 NEC: 0 \u2013 2 (12 augustus 2012)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2013\u201314 season====\nZiyech scored his first goal for Heerenveen in a 2\u20130 win over [[NAC Breda]], on 10 August 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/201670/eredivisie-nac-breda-sc-heerenveen/|title=NAC Breda \u2013 SC Heerenveen: 0 \u2013 2 (10 augustus 2013)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 23 August, Ziyech provided two assists in a 3\u20133 draw with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/719513/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2013-2014-SC-Heerenveen-Ajax|title=SC Heerenveen 3\u20133 Ajax \u2013 Eredivisie 2013/2014 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 8 November, Ziyech scored and provided an assist in a 5\u20132 win over [[RKC Waalwijk|Waalwijk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/719594/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2013-2014-SC-Heerenveen-RKC-Waalwijk|title=SC Heerenveen 5\u20132 RKC Waalwijk \u2013 Eredivisie 2013/2014 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 18 December, Ziyech scored two goals against [[AZ Alkmaar]], in the fourth round of the KNVB Cup, one in regular time and a last-minute penalty to draw level and take the game into a penalty shootout, but he missed his penalty and Heerenveen were knocked out 6\u20135 on penalties.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/215329/knvb-beker-az-sc-heerenveen/|title=AZ \u2013 SC Heerenveen: 2 \u2013 2 (18 december 2013)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 21 December, Ziyech scored twice and provided one assist in a 5\u20131 away win over [[AZ Alkmaar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/201813/eredivisie-az-sc-heerenveen/|title=AZ \u2013 SC Heerenveen: 1 \u2013 5 (21 december 2013)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 18 January 2014, Ziyech scored in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/719659/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2013-2014-SC-Heerenveen-Roda|title=SC Heerenveen 2\u20132 Roda \u2013 Eredivisie 2013/2014 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 9 February, he scored in a 3\u20131 win over [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/201865/eredivisie-fc-groningen-sc-heerenveen/|title=FC Groningen \u2013 SC Heerenveen: 1 \u2013 3 ( 9 februari 2014)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 27 April, Ziyech scored once and provided an assist in a 4\u20131 win over Utrecht, after coming on as a substitute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/719776/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2013-2014-SC-Heerenveen-FC-Utrecht|title=SC Heerenveen 4\u20131 FC Utrecht \u2013 Eredivisie 2013/2014 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/201947/eredivisie-sc-heerenveen-fc-utrecht/|title=SC Heerenveen \u2013 FC Utrecht: 4 \u2013 1 (27 april 2014)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Twente===\nOn 18 August 2014, Ziyech joined [[FC Twente|Twente]], signing on a three-year contract, and took the number 10 shirt.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nu.nl/sport/3855207/fc-twente-bevestigt-komst-ziyech-van-heerenveen.html|title=FC Twente bevestigt komst Ziyech van Heerenveen {{!}} NU \u2013 Het laatste nieuws het eerst op NU.nl|website=www.nu.nl|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\nOn 5 October, Ziyech scored once and provided an assist in a 2\u20132 draw with [[AZ Alkmaar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/825605/Live/-Eredivisie-2014-2015-AZ-Alkmaar-Twente|title=AZ Alkmaar 2\u20132 Twente \u2013 Eredivisie 2014/2015 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 6 March 2015, Ziyech scored twice in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/220494/eredivisie-willem-ii-fc-twente/|title=Willem II \u2013 FC Twente: 2 \u2013 2 ( 6 maart 2015)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 10 May, he provided three assists in a 3\u20130 home win over [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/220266/eredivisie-fc-twente-fc-dordrecht/|title=FC Twente \u2013 FC Dordrecht: 3 \u2013 0 (10 mei 2015)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/825682/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2014-2015-Twente-FC-Dordrecht|title=Twente 3\u20130 FC Dordrecht \u2013 Eredivisie 2014/2015 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 17 May, Ziyech scored twice and provided an assist in a 3\u20131 away win over his former club [[Heerenveen S.C.|Heerenveen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/220549/eredivisie-sc-heerenveen-fc-twente/|title=SC Heerenveen \u2013 FC Twente: 1 \u2013 3 (17 mei 2015)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/eredivisie-match-report-heerenveen-1-3-twente/|title=Eredivisie match report: Heerenveen 1\u20133 Twente \u2013 Football Oranje|date=17 May 2015|work=Football Oranje|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n====2015\u201316 season====\nFor the [[2015\u201316 FC Twente season|2015\u201316 season]], Ziyech was selected as captain of the club; however, he was stripped of the captaincy in early January 2016, after he made disrespectful comments against the club and publicly requesting a transfer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/twente-strip-ziyech-of-captaincy/|title=Twente strip Ziyech of captaincy \u2013 Football Oranje|date=4 January 2016|work=Football Oranje|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/dutch-eredivisie/123113/ziyech-stripped-captaincy/|title=Ziyech stripped of captaincy \u2013 FOX Sports Asia|date=6 January 2016|work=FOX Sports Asia|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> The 2015\u201316 season was the most prolific season in Ziyech's career, as he scored 17 goals and provided 10 assist in the Eredivisie.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Players/115868/History/Hakim-Ziyech|title=Hakim Ziyech \u2013 History|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Ajax===\nOn 30 August 2016, Ziyech signed for [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a five-year deal, with a reported transfer of \u20ac11m.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2016/08/hakim-ziyech-signs-to-ajax-for-a-reported-e11m/|title=Hakim Ziyech signs to Ajax for a reported \u20ac11m \u2013 DutchNews.nl|date=31 August 2016|work=DutchNews.nl|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/ziyech-ik-wil-bij-ajax-de-lijn-van-fc-twente-doortrekken|title=Privacyinstellingen op VI.nl|website=www.vi.nl|language=nl|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\nOn 15 September, Ziyech was given a red card in the 79th minute, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] in the opening group game of the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Europa League group stage#Group G|Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2017/matches/round=2000792/match=2019391/index.html|title=UEFA Europa League \u2013 Panathinaikos-Ajax|last=UEFA.com|website=UEFA.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> Six days later, on 21 September, he scored his first goal for Ajax in a 5\u20130 win over [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] in the [[2016\u201317 KNVB Cup#First round|KNVB Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1139165/Live/Netherlands-KNVB-Cup-2016-2017-Ajax-Willem-II|title=Ajax 5\u20130 Willem II \u2013 KNVB Cup 2016/2017 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 2 October, Ziyech scored his first league goal for the club in a 3\u20132 win over Utrecht.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-utrecht/356783|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 October, he scored in a 2\u20132 draw with [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] in the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Europa League group stage#Group G|Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/celta-vigo-vs-ajax/366992|title=Europa League (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 October, he scored in a 1\u20130 win over [[S.B.V. Excelsior|Excelsior]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-excelsior/356806|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 3 November, Ziyech scored in the reverse fixture against Celta Vigo in the Europa League, a 3\u20132 win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-celta-vigo/367014|title=Europa League (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 4 December, he scored a penalty in a 2\u20130 win over [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-groningen/356842|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 15 January 2017, Ziyech scored twice in a 3\u20131 away win over [[PEC Zwolle|Zwolle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/pec-zwolle-vs-ajax/356873|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 29 January, he scored in a 3\u20130 win over [[ADO Den Haag|Den Haag]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/256893/eredivisie-ajax-ado-den-haag/|title=Ajax \u2013 ADO Den Haag: 3 \u2013 0 (29 januari 2017)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 8 April, he scored in a 5\u20131 away win over [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/nec-vs-ajax/356979|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2017\u201318 season====\nOn 12 August 2017, Ziyech scored the opening goal in a 1\u20132 defeat to [[Heracles Almelo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/273610/eredivisie-heracles-almelo-ajax/|title=Heracles Almelo \u2013 Ajax: 2 \u2013 1 (12 augustus 2017)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 August, Ziyech scored in a 3\u20131 win over [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/273619/eredivisie-ajax-fc-groningen/|title=Ajax \u2013 FC Groningen: 3 \u2013 1 (20 augustus 2017)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 9 September, Ziyech missed a penalty but eventually scored just five minutes later in a 3\u20130 win over [[PEC Zwolle|Zwolle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-pec-zwolle/372816|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 18 November, Ziyech provided an assist in an 8\u20130 win over NAC Breda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/273709/eredivisie-nac-breda-ajax/|title=NAC Breda \u2013 Ajax: 0 \u2013 8 (18 november 2017)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42041711|title=NAC Breda 0\u20138 Ajax|date=18 November 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=6 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 26 November, he provided an assist in a 5\u20131 win over [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/273722/eredivisie-ajax-roda-jc/|title=Ajax \u2013 Roda JC: 5 \u2013 1 (26 november 2017)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42132045|title=Ajax 5\u20131 Roda JC Kerkrade|date=26 November 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=6 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 14 December, Ziyech scored in a 3\u20131 win over Excelsior.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1189178/Live/Netherlands-Eredivisie-2017-2018-Ajax-Excelsior|title=Ajax 3\u20131 Excelsior \u2013 Eredivisie 2017/2018 Live|website=www.whoscored.com|language=en|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 December, Ziyech missed a penalty against his former club [[FC Twente|Twente]], in the [[2017\u201318 KNVB Cup#Round of 16|round of sixteen]] of the [[2017\u201318 KNVB Cup|KNVB Cup]], with Ajax suffering elimination after losing the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballdatabase.eu/en/match/summary/1666293-ajax_amsterdam-fc_twente|title=FC Twente 1\u20131 Ajax Amsterdam / KNVB-Beker 2017/2018|website=www.footballdatabase.eu|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 4 February 2018, Ziyech scored an injury-time goal in a 3\u20131 win over [[NAC Breda]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbaluitslagen/273797/eredivisie-ajax-nac-breda/|title=Ajax \u2013 NAC Breda: 3 \u2013 1 ( 4 februari 2018)|website=FCUpdate.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/livematch/ajax-nac-breda/584049/|title=LiveMatch|website=fotbollskanalen|language=sv|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> Three days later, on 7 February, he scored in a 4\u20132 away win over Roda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/roda-jc-vs-ajax/372983|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 18 March, Ziyech scored twice in a 5\u20132 away win over [[Sparta Rotterdam]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sparta-rdm-vs-ajax/373040|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref> On 19 April, Ziyech scored in a 4\u20131 win over [[VVV-Venlo|Venlo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-vvv-venlo/373071|title=Eredivisie (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=6 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2018\u201319 season====\nOn 25 July 2018, Ziyech scored in a [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Q2 L2.1|2\u20130]] win over [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Second qualifying round|second qualifying round]] of the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/ajax-vs-sturm-graz/392391|title=Football (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports|language=en|access-date=23 August 2018}}</ref> On 22 August 2018, Ziyech scored in a [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#PO L2.1|3\u20131]] win over Dynamo Kyiv in the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|play-off round]] of the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45278848|title=Ajax 3-1 Dynamo Kiev: Ajax close on Champions League return|date=22 August 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=23 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 13 February 2019, he scored his first Champions League goal, scoring the equaliser in a 1\u20132 loss against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11636691/ajax-1-2-real-madrid-var-helps-madrid-to-edge-past-dutch-team|title=Ajax 1-2 Real Madrid: VAR helps Madrid to edge past Dutch team|website=Sky Sports|language=en|access-date=16 February 2019}}</ref> On 5 March 2019, he scored again in the 4\u20131 victory over Real Madrid in the second leg, which saw the title holders being knocked out and bringing Ajax to the quarter-finals, where they eliminated [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] to reach the semi\u2013finals of the competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/commentary?gameId=530625 |work=ESPN |title=Real Madrid vs. Ajax Amsterdam |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 April 2019, Ziyech assisted for the only goal in the Champions League semi\u2013final first leg win at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Taylor |first1=Daniel |title=Tottenham struggle for firepower after Donny van de Beek strikes early for Ajax |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/apr/30/tottenham-hotspur-ajax-champions-league-semi-final-first-leg-match-report |website=The Guardian |accessdate=12 August 2019 |date=30 April 2019}}</ref> He also scored the second goal for Ajax in the second leg of the semi-final, where Ajax were beaten 3\u20132 by Tottenham and were knocked out of the tournament on away goals with a 3\u20133 aggregate score.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnston |first1=Neil |title=Ajax 2-3 Tottenham (3-3 on aggregate - Spurs win on away goals): Lucas Moura scores dramatic winner |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48192369 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=12 August 2019 |date=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Portugal-Morocco by soccer.ru 8 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Ziyech playing for Morocco at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].|alt=|230x230px]]\n\n====2019\u201320 season====\nIn August 2019, he signed a new three-year contract with Ajax.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49312656|title=Hakim Ziyech: Moroccan scores in Ajax win after signing new deal|date=11 August 2019|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=27 August 2019|first=Mark|last=Gleeson}}</ref>\n\n===Chelsea===\nOn 14 February 2020, it was announced that Ajax and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] had reached an agreement for the transfer of Ziyech for a fee of \u20ac40 million (potentially increasing to a maximum of \u20ac44 million, with variable factors). The player will join the Premier League club from the 2020\u201321 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.ajax.nl/streams/ajax-now/ajax-and-chelsea-reach-agreement-for-ziyech-.htm|title=Ajax and Chelsea reach agreement for Ziyech|website=Ajax English|language=en-US|access-date=14 February 2020}}</ref> Ten days later, Chelsea announced they had agreed personal terms with Ziyech and that he had signed five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shread |first1=Joe |title=Hakim Ziyech signs five-year Chelsea deal ahead of summer move |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11668/11941864/hakim-ziyech-signs-five-year-chelsea-deal-ahead-of-summer-move |website=Sky Sports |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n\n===Netherlands===\nZiyech was eligible to play for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] or [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref name=\"Football Oranje\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/ziyech-added-to-netherlands-squad/|title=Ziyech added to Netherlands squad \u2013 Football Oranje|date=19 May 2015|work=Football Oranje|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Ziyech played for Dutch national youth teams, playing for the U19s, U20s and [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|U21s]]. He received his first call-up to the senior squad in May 2015, for friendly matches against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] and [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]].<ref name=\"Football Oranje\"/>\n\n===Morocco===\n[[File:Portugal-Morocco by soccer.ru 8.jpg|thumb|Hakim Ziyech (shirt number 7) \u2013 pictured with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] \u2013 against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]\n[[File:Spain vs Morocco (17).jpg|thumb|Hakim Ziyech playing for [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] against [[Spain national team|Spain]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]\nIn September 2015, Ziyech confirmed his choice to represent [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] at the international stage.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/34349063|title=Is the Dutch national team set to lose players to Morocco?|date=24 September 2015|work=BBC Sport|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/ziyech-to-turn-his-back-on-netherlands-to-represent-morocco/|title=Ziyech to turn his back on Netherlands to represent Morocco \u2013 Football Oranje|date=20 September 2015|work=Football Oranje|access-date=6 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Ziyech made his debut for the national team on 9 October, in a 1\u20130 defeat to [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/10/09/world/friendlies/morocco/cote-divoire/2124893/|title=Morocco vs. C\u00f4te d'Ivoire \u2013 9 October 2015 \u2013 Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 27 May 2016, he scored his first two goals for Morocco, in a 2\u20130 win over [[Congo national football team|Congo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=448839|title=Morocco vs. Congo \u2013 Football Match Summary \u2013 May 27, 2016 \u2013 ESPN|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018}}</ref> On 4 September, Ziyech scored in a 2\u20130 win over [[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe national football team|S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]] in a [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualifying]] match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.com/m/29894/2016-09-04/afcon-qualification/morocco/sao-tome-e-principe|title=Morocco vs S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 e Pr\u00edncipe 2 \u2013 0 {{!}} AFCON Qualification {{!}} 2017 Gabon {{!}} Group Stage {{!}} World Football|website=www.worldfootball.com|language=en|access-date=3 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803163612/http://www.worldfootball.com/m/29894/2016-09-04/afcon-qualification/morocco/sao-tome-e-principe|archive-date=3 August 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> Ziyech was not selected for [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations squads#Morocco|the final 23-man squad]] for the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://video.kwesesports.com/afcon/article/has-renard-made-a-glaring-error-with-ziyech-snub|title=Has Renard made a glaring error with Ziyech snub?|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803163516/http://video.kwesesports.com/afcon/article/has-renard-made-a-glaring-error-with-ziyech-snub|archive-date=3 August 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 September 2017, Ziyech scored in a 6\u20130 win over [[Mali national football team|Mali]], in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Third Round|qualifying match]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2017/09/227626/world-cup-2018-qualifiers-morocco-crush-mali-6-0/|title=World Cup 2018 Qualifiers : Morocco Crush Mali 6\u20130|date=1 September 2017|work=Morocco World News|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41131515|title=2018 World Cup: Morocco thrash Mali as Tunisia and Cape Verde also win|date=2 September 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> He was selected for the final [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Morocco|23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad \u2013 Final 23-man lists {{!}} Goal.com|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12098/11374464/every-world-cup-squad-listed-brazil-france-spain-and-more|title=Every World Cup 2018 squad listed: Brazil, France, Spain and more|work=Sky Sports|access-date=3 August 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|7 March 2020}}<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|hakim-ziyech}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/hakim-ziyech/255713// |title=Nederland \u2013 H.Ziyech \u2013 Profile with news, career statistics and history |website=Soccerway |accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<sup>1</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>2</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Heerenveen season|2012\u201313]]\n|3||0||1||0||2||0||2||0||8||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Heerenveen s