ident Donald Trump's political rally in Cincinnati|last=Bailey|first=Phillip M.|website=The Courier-Journal|language=en|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|Thursday, August 15, 2019\n| [[Manchester, New Hampshire|Manchester]]\n| [[New Hampshire|NH]]\n| [[SNHU Arena]]\n| 11,000\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-rally-manchester-new-hampshire-today-maga-2020-campaign-snhu-arena-live-stream-updates-2019-08-15/|title=Trump tells backers reelecting him is critical for their pocketbooks|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|Monday, September 9, 2019\n| [[Fayetteville, North Carolina|Fayetteville]]\n| [[North Carolina|NC]]\n| Crown Expo Center\n| 5,500\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/election/article234445702.html|title=President Trump will rally for Dan Bishop in Fayetteville on election eve|last=Morrill|first=Jim|date=2019-08-27|website=The News&Observer|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828201323/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/election/article234445702.html|archive-date=2019-08-28|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|Monday, September 16, 2019\n| [[Rio Rancho, New Mexico|Rio Rancho]]\n| [[New Mexico|NM]]\n| [[Santa Ana Star Center]]\n| 8,000\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kvia.com/your-voice-your-vote/campaign-2020/2019/09/07/president-trump-to-hold-campaign-rally-in-new-mexico-later-this-month/|title=President Trump to hold campaign rally in New Mexico later this month|last=|first=|date=2019-09-07|website=KVIA ABC-7|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|Thursday, October 10, 2019\n| [[Minneapolis, Minnesota|Minneapolis]]\n| [[Minnesota|MN]]\n| [[Target Center]]\n| 20,000\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.twincities.com/2019/09/26/trump-announces-minneapolis-rally-at-target-center-in-october/|title=Trump announces Minneapolis rally at Target Center in October|date=2019-09-26|website=Twin Cities|language=en-US|access-da